al seismicity, where few three-component stations are\navailable. The results obtained here could help to extend the applicability of\nthese methodologies to other sites of engineering interest.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 26 Feb 2014 16:48:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 27 May 2016 04:26:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-30"}
